column10: Serum beta-2-microglobulin (beta-2-M) <4 mcg/mL is a good prognostic factor in patients with multiple myeloma. column10: Those with blood type O may have lower normal von willebrand factor ranging from 40%-50%. Laboratory diagnosis relies on detection of parallel decreases in VWF level and the absence of notable anomalies in the distribution or structure of the VWF multimers. Given that individuals with Type O blood have normal VWF level as low as 40%, an accurate diagnosis requires the study of family medical history and bleeding score.
